## 7. FastAPI server endpoints

```
POST /register          → upsert hardware_config, return api_key + hw_id mapping
GET  /health            → {"status": "ok", "mode": "server"}  (agents use this for mode detection)
GET  /get-job           → returns next queued job for this hw_id, or {"job": null} if none/busy
POST /job-status        → agent reports job started/completed/failed
POST /bulk-sync         → receives full sync payload, inserts all tables idempotently
POST /experiments/submit → researcher submits experiment to global queue
GET  /experiments/queue → admin sees pending submissions
POST /experiments/approve/{id}  → admin approves → promotes to job_queue
POST /experiments/reject/{id}   → admin rejects with notes
GET  /machines          → list all registered machines with status (for Streamlit dashboard)
GET  /machines/{hw_id}/runs → runs for a specific machine (Streamlit per-machine view)
```

